<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-12-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-12-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="1703" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1703">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 834.00/118.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Montevideo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-12-12">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 12, 1911</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>At the request of the Diplomatic Corps, the Argentine and Brazilian naval
                            commanders at Asuncion have forbidden revolutionist war vessels to shell
                            the city and unfortified places. Brazil will send more war vessels.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Grevstad.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>